Html:
I am using verion 1.7.0 and itterating through a array returned form a database, it has 68 columns and 831 rows. The code using is below. If you notice in the output, memory is neglible by PHP's mesaure, then all of a sudden it spikes, going up .25 megs every 4 rows. I have no idea what is wrong, but this seems to huge memory usage for that size dataset.

Any help is greatly appreciated,

Mike

----

Code

----

print "BEFORE ".(memory_get_usage(true) / 1024 / 1024)."<br>";

  foreach ($dbResult as $fields) {
   $col = 0;

   foreach ($fields as $field) {
    $objExcel->getActiveSheet()->setCellValueExplicitByColumnAndRow($col, $row, $field, PHPExcel_Cell_DataType::TYPE_STRING);
    $col++;
   }

print "AFTER EACH ROW ".(memory_get_usage(true) / 1024 / 1024)."<br>";

   $row++;
  }

You must estimate approximately 1KB memory usage per cell. With 68 columns, that fits pretty well with .25MB per 4 rows like you are saying.

We wish to reduce memory usage via a cache provider for the collection of cells. See this work item

http://phpexcel.codeplex.com/WorkItem/View.aspx?WorkItemId=6857

Until then, I'm afraid there is no solution to reduce memory usage.
